Package com.cafean.client.analysis

Class ConditionSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.client.analysis.GenericObject
      • com.cafean.client.analysis.ConditionSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IdentHolder, ChannelDataHolder, java.lang.Cloneable, javax.swing.undo.StateEditable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PartialConditionSet
    public class ConditionSet
extends GenericObject
implements ChannelDataHolder
    This data structure holds the set of initial conditions for the plugin. These values are stored internally in a hashtable but the data structure is designed to be overwritten with a subblock in DDT.

      • setKeys

        public void setKeys​(java.lang.String[] val_)
        This method sets the key array that will be used to store all of the data inside this condition set. This defines a transient array that will be used to rebuild the hashtable after the values are defined.
        Parameters:
        val_ - the String[] containing all of the keys for the current conditions. These keys should be the channel names that will be used to identify the properties.

      • getValues

      • setValues

        public void setValues​(double[] values)

        Parameters:
        values - the double[] containing all of the data.
